-- Russian Railways to Increase 2012 Investment to $13.7 Billion
-- B y   B r a d   C o o k
-- 2011-12-26T07:19:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-26/russian-railways-to-increase-2012-investment-to-13-7-billion.html
OAO Russian Railways, the country’s
rail monopoly, plans to boost its investment program next year
to 428 billion rubles ($13.7 billion) to improve cargo handling,
the state-run company said in a statement today.  That’s 32 billion rubles more than this year, Russian
Railways said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
